    Layout = null;
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <title>Sage 300c Customization</title>
    <link href="~/Areas/CU/Assets/Styles/css/default.min.css" rel="stylesheet" />
</head>

<body class="master-stand-alone">

<header>
    <div class="header-global">
        <div class="wrapper">
            <div class="Sage_logo"><img src="~/Areas/CU/Assets/Images/sage_300_logo_white.png" height="25" alt="Sage 300"></div>
            <div class="top-nav">
                <ul>
                    <li id="liAdminHelp">
                        <i class="help"><span>Help</span></i>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</header>

<section class="main-body">
    <div class="wrapper">
        <h1 class="page-header">Sage 300 UI Customization Data Access Layer</h1>
        <ul>
            <li>This sample code to use Sage SAMLTD database and Order Entry screen to show</li> 
            <ul>
                <li>Access Sage300c service and endpoints to get data</li>
                <li>Access custom view to get data</li>
                <li>Use Sage 300c common services query to get data</li>
                <li>Use Entity Framework to get data</li> 
            </ul>
            <li>Sign in to Sage 300c, <a href= @ViewBag.Sage300Url>Sage 300c</a>, and open the Order Entry screen</li>
            <ul>
                <li>Sage 300c parses the settings files to add controls to the screen and view, </li>
                <li>and to include the JavaScript file in the view.</li>
            </ul>
            <li>All the DAL code in Areas\CU\DAL and called by ISV1CustomizationController</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="footer">
    <div class="wrapper">
        <a class="logo-sage" href="http://na.sage.com"><img src="~/Areas/CU/Assets/Images/footer_logo.png" width="60" height="25" alt="Sage"></a>
